Familiarize yourself with the different educational tracks available, including:
1) Two-year and four-year colleges: Community colleges and universities offer a variety of degree options;
2) Career and technical programs: These programs provide specialized training for specific careers;
3) Dual enrollment and AP courses: High school students can earn college credits early by taking these advanced courses;
4) Early college programs: Some schools allow students to complete college coursework alongside high school requirements.

